ANTHRAX, HIPPOPOTAMUS - UGANDA (08): (KALANGALA) SUSPECTED
**********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: 17 Oct 2010
Source: Ultimate Media Consult [edited]
<http://www.ugpulse.com/articles/daily/news.asp?about=Two+hippos+die+in+Kalangala&ID=16149>


Two hippos have died of suspected anthrax at Nkibanga island in
Kalangala district. The district is surrounded by Lake Victoria. The
death of the hippos brings the death toll to 14 since the beginning
of July 2010.

The MP for Kyamuswa, Moses Kabuusu, has said the district leaders
have not established whether the animals have died of anthrax.

Recently, many hippos died of suspected anthrax in Western Uganda.
Uganda Wildlife Authority is investigating the death of the hippos.

